## Vue Component Patterns in Socialaize

Based on analysis of actual components, here are the patterns:

### 1. **Simple UI Component** (DangerButton.vue)

```typescript
<script setup lang="ts">
import { computed } from "vue";
import { Icon } from "@iconify/vue";

const props = defineProps<{
  text: string;
  icon?: string;
  iconPosition?: "left" | "right";
  iconClass?: string;
  buttonClass?: string;
  loading?: boolean;
  disabled?: boolean;
}>();

const disabled = computed(() => {
  return props.disabled;
});
</script>
```

**Patterns:**
- ‚úÖ `<script setup lang="ts">` with Composition API
- ‚úÖ Type-only `defineProps<{}>` (no runtime)
- ‚úÖ All props fully typed with optional `?` markers
- ‚úÖ No explicit emits (simple component)

---

### 2. **Complex Input Component** (SearchableDropdown.vue)

```typescript
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref, computed, watch, nextTick } from "vue";
import { useMounted } from "@vueuse/core";
import { useFloating, offset, flip, shift } from "@floating-ui/vue";
import { Icon } from "@iconify/vue";

interface Option {
  value: string;
  label: string;
  isDefault?: boolean;
}

const props = defineProps<{
  options: Option[];
  isValidTest?: (value: string | string[]) => boolean;
  isValid?: boolean;
  placeholder?: string;
  icon?: string;
  label?: string;
  loading?: boolean;
  description?: string;
  required?: boolean;
  disabled?: boolean;
  invalidMessage?: string;
  customClass?: string;
  multiple?: boolean;
}>();

// defineModel for v-model support
const modelValue = defineModel<string | string[]>("modelValue", { default: "" });

const searchQuery = ref("");
const mounted = useMounted();
const isOpen = ref(false);
// ... more refs
```

**Patterns:**
- ‚úÖ Local interfaces defined in same file
- ‚úÖ `defineModel<>()` for v-model (Vue 3.3+)
- ‚úÖ Complex union types (`string | string[]`)
- ‚úÖ Function types in props (`isValidTest?: (value: ...) => boolean`)
- ‚úÖ VueUse composables (`useMounted`)

---

### 3. **Modal Feature Component** (CreateTeamModal.vue)

```typescript
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref } from 'vue';
import BaseModal from '@/components/vue/modals/BaseModal.vue';
import TextInput from '@/components/vue/inputs/TextInput.vue';
import PrimaryButton from '@/components/vue/buttons/PrimaryButton.vue';
import OutlineButton from '@/components/vue/buttons/OutlineButton.vue';

defineProps<{
    isLoading: boolean;
}>();

const isOpen = defineModel('isOpen', {
    default: false,
    required: true,
});

const emit = defineEmits<{
    'submit': [name: string];
}>();

const teamName = ref('');

const handleClose = () => {
    isOpen.value = false;
    teamName.value = '';
};

const handleCreate = () => {
    if (!teamName.value) return;
    emit('submit', teamName.value);
};
</script>
```

**Patterns:**
- ‚úÖ Typed `defineEmits<{}>` with tuple syntax for event payloads
- ‚úÖ `defineModel()` for two-way binding
- ‚úÖ Simple local state with `ref()`
- ‚úÖ Event handlers as functions (not inline)

---

### 4. **Complex Card Component** (BaseProviderCard.vue)

```typescript
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref, computed } from "vue";
import { useMounted, computedAsync } from "@vueuse/core";
import { Icon } from "@iconify/vue";
import { getPlatformAccountById, getDisplayName } from "@/utils/providerUtils";

const props = defineProps<{
    accountId: string;
    showDisconnect?: boolean;
    showProfilePicture?: boolean;
    showStacked?: boolean;
    allowSelection?: boolean;
    class?: string;
    platformType: string;
}>();

const emit = defineEmits<{
    (e: "disconnect", accountId: string): void;
}>();

const loading = ref(true);
const error = ref<string | undefined>();
const mounted = useMounted();
const selected = defineModel<boolean>("selected", { required: false, default: false });
const displayName = ref("");

const accountData = computedAsync<any | undefined>(
    async () => {
        if (!mounted.value || !props.accountId) {
            return undefined;
        }
        try {
            const platformAccount = await getPlatformAccountById(props.accountId);
            displayName.value = getDisplayName(platformAccount, props.platformType);
            return platformAccount;
        } catch (err) {
            console.error(`Error fetching ${props.platformType} account data:`, err);
            error.value = "Failed to load account data";
        }
    },
    undefined,
    loading
);
```

**Patterns:**
- ‚úÖ Async data with `computedAsync` from VueUse
- ‚úÖ Generic types on refs (`ref<string | undefined>()`)
- ‚úÖ Scoped styles section present
- ‚úÖ Named slots with scoped data

---

## Summary

**TypeScript Strictness:** VERY STRICT
- All props use type-only `defineProps<{}>` (no runtime validation)
- Complex types: unions, generics, function signatures
- Typed emits with payload tuples
- Explicit return types on computed/async functions

**Composition API:** 100% `<script setup>`
- Vue 3.3+ features (`defineModel`)
- VueUse composables everywhere (`useMounted`, `computedAsync`)
- No Options API found

**Typical Structure:**
1. Imports
2. Local interfaces (if needed)
3. `defineProps<{}>`
4. `defineModel()` (if v-model)
5. `defineEmits<{}>` (if events)
6. Reactive state (`ref`, `computed`)
7. Functions/handlers
8. Lifecycle (via composables, not explicit hooks)

